    Preface




Xaraya 1.0 was released in November 2005.
    The release marked the culmination of Xaraya's transformation from a
    simple open source content management system into an enterprise level,
    extensible, application framework. Since the 1.0 release there has been
    ongoing improvements in stability, performance, and security. Xaraya now
    provides a reliable, flexible and rapid development platform that web
    application developers have learned they can depend on for projects of
    varying size and complexity.


Xaraya is written in PHP, platform independent and currently can be
    installed with a variety of databases including MySQL, PostgreSQL, and SQLite. It is
    licensed under the GNU
    General Public License.


This Xaraya Developer Guide is written in the hope it will assist
    existing and budding developers that wish to learn how to use Xaraya to
    create custom web based applications. The Xaraya Developer Guide provides
    a guide to best practice in Xaraya development along with the information
    to understand and use the Xaraya development framework for developing web
    applications.


The Xaraya Documentation team welcome feedback and suggestions for
    improvement. All feature requests and notification of corrections can be
    lodged in the Support Documentation component on Xaraya's bugzilla










